  "body": "### Component\n\nCast\n\n### Describe the feature you would like\n\nSome `CREATE2` factories like [0age's](https://etherscan.io/address/0x0000000000ffe8b47b3e2130213b802212439497) require that the upper 20 bytes of the `bytes32` salt be the same as the caller's address.\r\n\r\nSome factories like [`maldon`](https://github.com/flood-protocol/maldon) provide a `--caller` argument that allows for compatibility with these factories. \r\n\r\nThis functionality should be added to `cast create2`. I think the ideal flow here would be to have the salt contain the address if `--caller` is provided.\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
